metadata.description: Historical percentage of S&P 500 stocks near 52-week highs and lows

interpretation.high_percentage_near_highs: >10% of stocks at highs indicates strong leadership and healthy market
interpretation.high_percentage_near_lows: >10% of stocks at lows suggests broad weakness and distribution
interpretation.high_ratio_above_2: Strong market with good breadth - more stocks leading higher
interpretation.low_ratio_below_0.5: Weak market with poor breadth - more stocks at lows than highs
interpretation.extremes: Very high readings (>15%) at either extreme can signal potential reversals
interpretation.divergence: Index at new high but few stocks participating = bearish divergence

field_descriptions.near_52w_high: Data for stocks within 1% of their 52-week high
field_descriptions.near_52w_low: Data for stocks within 1% of their 52-week low
field_descriptions.count: Number of stocks meeting the criteria
field_descriptions.percentage: Percentage of S&P 500 stocks meeting the criteria
field_descriptions.high_low_ratio: Ratio of stocks near highs to stocks near lows (higher = stronger)
